  "local_port": 55810,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are good pranks at night?",
  "response": "Pranks can be fun as long as they are harmless and respectful. Here are some light-hearted pranks suitable for nighttime:\n\n1. **Balloon Room**:\n   Fill someone's room with balloons while they're asleep. When they wake up, they'll be surprised to see their room transformed into a sea of balloons.\n\n2. **Fake Spiders or Bugs**:\n   Place realistic-looking fake spiders or bugs around their bed or room. This can give them a harmless scare when they turn on the light.\n\n3. **Oreo Toothpaste**:\n   Replace the cream in Oreo cookies with white toothpaste. Offer them as a late-night snack. It's funny to see their reaction when they bite into it.\n\n4. **Bed Swap**:\n   If you have bunk beds or multiple beds in a room, switch the positions of the sleepers while they are deeply asleep (make sure they are okay with this type of prank).\n\n5. **Voice-Activated Confetti**:\n   Set up a small confetti cannon connected to a voice-activated device. When the person says a certain word or phrase in the morning, the confetti goes off.\n\n6. **Glowing Eyes**:\n   Cut eye holes in a white sheet, put it over your head, and use a flashlight or glow sticks to make the eyes glow. Silently sneak around and watch their reactions when they see \"floating eyes\" in the dark.\n\n7. **Whoopee Cushion Under the Pillow**:\n   Place a whoopee cushion under their pillow. When they lay their head down, it will make a funny noise.\n\nRemember, the key to a good prank is to keep it fun and harmless. Make sure the person you are pranking can take a joke and won\u2019t be too scared or upset by the prank. Always prioritize safety and respect.",
